{
  "name": "8 — HubSpot API test (deals + contacts)",
  "nodes": [
    {
      "parameters": {},
      "id": "manual_trigger",
      "name": "Run now",
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.manualTrigger",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "position": [200, 300]
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "method": "GET",
        "url": "https://api.hubapi.com/crm/v3/objects/deals",
        "authentication": "genericCredentialType",
        "genericAuthType": "httpHeaderAuth",
        "sendQuery": true,
        "queryParameters": {
          "parameters": [
            { "name": "limit", "value": "10" },
            { "name": "properties", "value": "dealname,amount,dealstage,pipeline,closedate" }
          ]
        },
        "options": {}
      },
      "id": "list_deals",
      "name": "1. List deals (pipeline)",
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.httpRequest",
      "typeVersion": 4.2,
      "position": [440, 220],
      "credentials": { "httpHeaderAuth": { "id": "HS_CRED", "name": "HubSpot" } }
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "method": "GET",
        "url": "https://api.hubapi.com/crm/v3/objects/contacts",
        "authentication": "genericCredentialType",
        "genericAuthType": "httpHeaderAuth",
        "sendQuery": true,
        "queryParameters": {
          "parameters": [
            { "name": "limit", "value": "10" },
            { "name": "properties", "value": "firstname,lastname,email,jobtitle,company" }
          ]
        },
        "options": {}
      },
      "id": "list_contacts",
      "name": "2. List contacts",
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.httpRequest",
      "typeVersion": 4.2,
      "position": [440, 400],
      "credentials": { "httpHeaderAuth": { "id": "HS_CRED", "name": "HubSpot" } }
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "## HubSpot API test\n\n**Setup:** create an n8n credential of type **Header Auth**, named **HubSpot**:\n- Name: `Authorization`\n- Value: `Bearer <your HubSpot private-app token>`\n\nThen select it on both HTTP nodes and **Run now**.\n\n**Expect:** node 1 returns your deals (pipeline) with dealname/amount/stage; node 2 returns contacts. This shows how deals + contacts are structured, so we can map the opportunity write-back later.\n\nDocs: HubSpot CRM v3 — /crm/v3/objects/deals and /contacts.",
        "height": 280,
        "width": 360
      },
      "id": "note",
      "name": "How to test",
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "position": [800, 240]
    }
  ],
  "connections": {
    "Run now": { "main": [[
      { "node": "1. List deals (pipeline)", "type": "main", "index": 0 },
      { "node": "2. List contacts", "type": "main", "index": 0 }
    ]] }
  },
  "settings": { "executionOrder": "v1" }
}
